    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-01-26T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-01-26T18:00:00-05:00" n="575"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d575">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">887.00 <gloss target="#t_TA1">TA</gloss>/1–2651:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Lebanon</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_BJH1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bruins</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d575fn1">Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_CHB1">Harlan B.
                            Clark</persName>, Officer in Charge of Lebanon–Syria–Iraq
                        Affairs.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-01-26T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >January 26, 1951—6 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>517. ReDeptel 501 Jan 24.<note n="2" xml:id="d575fn2">Not printed; it treated the
                        subject of Communist aggression in Korea. (693.95/1–1851)</note> Dept
                    continues believe early signature <gloss target="#t_FCN1">FCN</gloss> Treaty and
                    Point Four General Agreement wld be excellent practicable means strengthening
                    US-Leb relations. Point Four Program for Leb can be implemented only after Leb
                    signs General Agreement.</p>
                <p>Suggest you discussing foregoing with Leb Govt.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_ADG1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
